      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly correspond to clinical decision metric (hemolysis index); mapping between model outputs and device performance metric documented.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH), which directly maps to the clinical hemolysis threshold. The correspondence between CFD shear stress fields and NIH is documented and reviewed. QoI relevance meets MRL 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
