      "rationale": "An independent CFD analyst reviewed simulation setup files and boundary condition assignments. No discrepancies found. Use error controls meet the required level 2 for this factor at MRL 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified; non-Newtonian blood rheology model evaluated; sensitivity of hemolysis prediction to model form documented.",
      "rationale": "The k-omega SST turbulence model was selected based on prior pump literature. A Newtonian blood assumption was adopted; sensitivity analysis showed up to 15% variation in NIH predictions when switching to a Carreau-Yasuda model, indicating model form uncertainty exceeds accepted bounds. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material and fluid properties documented with sources; uncertainty in inputs propagated through Monte Carlo analysis.",
      "rationale": "Blood density, nominal viscosity, and pump geometry inputs are documented with literature sources and manufacturing tolerances. Monte Carlo UQ with 500 samples was performed propagating input uncertainty to NIH predictions. Achieved level meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test sample characteristics documented; blood analog fluid composition reported with hematocrit equivalent.",
      "rationale": "Bench tests used a glycerol-water blood analog at 37% hematocrit equivalent. Sample preparation and lot traceability documented. Test sample factor meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Correspondence between experimental input parameters and simulation boundary conditions established; any discrepancies quantified.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team determined that patient-specific variation in blood viscosity and hematocrit does not apply to a pump-level CFD model operating on mean physiological values, and therefore this factor was not carried forward into the formal assessment. The team's position is that the factor is irrelevant to the COU because the model does not represent individual patient physiology. However, this determination has not been encoded as factorStatus 'not-applicable' as the standard requires, and no formal applicability argument has been documented. The factor therefore remains not-assessed at Model Risk Level 3, where unassessed factors represent a material epistemic gap."
    }
